bayStackIpv6MldSnoopingMib.name: bayStackIpv6MldSnoopingMib

revisions.description: Ver 5: Inverted the syntaxes for bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheType and bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheMode objects
Ver 4: Added bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceFlushPorts object, bsIpv6MldSnoopingFlushPorts scalar object

Ver 3: Added bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheTable, bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceFlush object, bsIpv6MldSnoopingFlush scalar object; Updated bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceOperationalVersion, bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceSendQuery, bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceProxy objects descriptions

bayStackIpv6MldSnoopingMib.description: This MIB module is used for IPv6 MLD Snooping configuration.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceTable.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceTable
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing IPv6 MLD Snooping interfaces.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceEntry.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceEntry
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an IPv6 MLD Snooping interface.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIfIndex.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIfIndex
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIfIndex.description: The internetwork-layer interface value of the interface for which IPv6 MLD Snooping is enabled.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQueryInterval.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQueryInterval
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IPv6 MLD Snooping Host-Query packets are transmitted on this interface.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceVersion.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceVersion
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceVersion.description: The version of IPv6 MLD Snooping which is running on this interface. This object is a place holder to allow for new versions of MLD to be introduced. Version 1 of MLD is defined in RFC 2710.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQuerier.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQuerier
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQuerier.description: The address of the IPv6 MLD Snooping Querier on the IPv6 subnet to which this interface is attached.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQueryMaxRespon.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQueryMaxResponseDelay
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQueryMaxRespon.description: The maximum query response time advertised in IPv6 MLD Snooping queries on this interface.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceJoins.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceJoins
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceJoins.description: The number of times a group membership has been added on this interface; that is, the number of times an entry for this interface has been added to the Cache Table. This object gives an indication of the amount of MLD activity over time.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceGroups.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceGroups
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceGroups.description: The current number of entries for this interface in the Cache Table.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceRobustness.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceRobustness
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IPv6 MLD Snooping is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses. The discussion of the Robustness Variable is in Section 7.1 of RFC 2710.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceLastListenQuer.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceLastListenQueryIntvl
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceLastListenQuer.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Delay inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages. This value may be tuned to modify the leave latency of the network. A reduced value results in reduced time to detect the loss of the last member of a group.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceProxyIfIndex.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceProxyIfIndex
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceProxyIfIndex.description: Some devices implement a form of MLD proxying whereby memberships learned on the interface represented by this row, cause MLD Multicast Listener Reports to be sent on the internetwork-layer interface identified by this object. Such a device would implement mldRouterMIBGroup only on its router interfaces (those interfaces with non-zero mldInterfaceProxyIfIndex). Typically, the value of this object is 0, indicating that no proxying is being done.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQuerierUpTime.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQuerierUpTime
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQuerierUpTime.description: The time since mldInterfaceQuerier was last changed.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQuerierExpiryT.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQuerierExpiryTime
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceQuerierExpiryT.description: The time remaining before the Other Querier Present Timer expires. If the local system is the querier, the value of this object is zero.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceEnabled.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceEnabled
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceEnabled.description: This object controls whether IPv6 MLD Snooping is enabled on this interface.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIgmpMRouterPor.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIgmpMRouterPorts
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIgmpMRouterPor.description: The set of ports in this interface that provide connectivity to an IPv6 Multicast router.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIgmpActiveMRou.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIgmpActiveMRouterPorts
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIgmpActiveMRou.description: The set of active ports in this interface that provide connectivity to an IPv6 Multicast router.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIgmpMRouterExp.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIgmpMRouterExpiration
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceIgmpMRouterExp.description: Multicast querier router aging time out.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceOperationalVer.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceOperationalVersion
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceOperationalVer.description: The operational version of IPv6 MLD Snooping which is running on this interface at the moment.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceSendQuery.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceSendQuery
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceSendQuery.description: This object controls whether IPv6 MLD Send-Query is enabled on this interface.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceProxy.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceProxy
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceProxy.description: This object controls whether IPv6 MLD Proxy is enabled on this interface.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceFlush.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceFlush
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceFlush.description: This object is used to remove MLD members from this interface. noAction(1) value is returned at read. all(4) value is used to flush groups and mrouters.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceFlushPorts.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceFlushPorts
bsIpv6MldSnoopingInterfaceFlushPorts.description: The set of ports in this interface that are going to be flushed. An empty port set is returned at read.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheTable.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheTable
bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IPv6 multicast groups for which there are members on a particular interface.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheEntry.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheEntry
bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheTable.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheAddress.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheAddress
bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheAddress.description: The IPv6 multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheIfIndex.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheIfIndex
bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheIfIndex.description: The internetwork-layer interface for which this entry contains information for an IPv6 multicast group address.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheSelf.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheSelf
bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheSelf.description: An indication of whether the local system is a member of this group address on this interface.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheLastReporter.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheLastReporter
bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheLastReporter.description: The IPv6 address of the source of the last membership report received for this IPv6 Multicast group address on this interface. If no membership report has been received, this object has the value 0::0.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheUpTime.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheUpTime
bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheUpTime.description: The time elapsed since this entry was created.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheExpiryTime.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheExpiryTime
bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. A value of 0 indicates that the entry is only present because bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheSelf is true and that if the router left the group, this entry would be aged out immediately. Note that some implementations may process Membership Reports from the local system in the same way as reports from other hosts, so a value of 0 is not required.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheStatus.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheStatus
bsIpv6MldSnoopingCacheStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or existing entries deleted from this table.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupTable.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupTable
bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing IPv6 MLD Snooping IGMP groups.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupEntry.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupEntry
bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an IPv6 MLD Snooping IGMP group.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupIpv6Address.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupIpv6Address
bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupIpv6Address.description: Multicast group Address (Class D) that others want to join. A group address can be the same for many incoming ports.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupMembers.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupMembers
bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupMembers.description: IPv6 Address of a source that has sent group report wishing to join this group.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupIfIndex.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupIfIndex
bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupIfIndex.description: An unique value to identify a physical interface or a logical interface (VLAN), which has received Group reports from various sources.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupInPort.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupInPort
bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupInPort.description: Value to identify physical interfaces or logical interfaces (VLANs), which has received Group reports from various sources.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupExpiration.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupExpiration
bsIpv6MldSnoopingIgmpGroupExpiration.description: Time left before the group report expired on this port. Only one of this variable port. This variable is updated upon receiving a group report.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheTable.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheTable
bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IPv6 multicast groups for which the switch is registered in order to receive the multicast traffic.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheEntry.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheEntry
bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheTable.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheIfIndex.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheIfIndex
bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheIfIndex.description: An unique value to identify a logical interface (VLAN) which is registered as MLD host for receiving multicast traffic

bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheGroupAddress.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheGroupAddress
bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheGroupAddress.description: The IPv6 destination address of the multicast traffic that the interface is registered for receiving it.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheSourceAddress.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheSourceAddress
bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheSourceAddress.description: The IPv6 source address of the multicast traffic that the interface is registered for receiving it.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheType.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheType
bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheType.description: The entry registration type (static or dynamic).

bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheMode.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheMode
bsIpv6MldSnoopingProxyCacheMode.description: Proxy mode for MLDv2 entries. version1(1) value is returned for MLDv1 entries

bsIpv6MldSnoopingFlush.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingFlush
bsIpv6MldSnoopingFlush.description: This object is used to remove MLD members from all the interfaces. noAction(1) value is returned at read. all(4) value is used to flush groups and mrouters.

bsIpv6MldSnoopingFlushPorts.name: bsIpv6MldSnoopingFlushPorts
bsIpv6MldSnoopingFlushPorts.description: The set of ports from all interfaces that are going to be flushed. An empty port set is returned at read.
